cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about computational color constancy, which is a fundamental problem in computer vision. The proposed method uses deep convolutional neural networks (CNN) to learn a robust regressor for color constancy. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The method also involves structured-output regression learning, which suggests that it may belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the use of CNNs for feature extraction and regression suggests that it may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
